## Why This Is Asked

Tests the ability to architect a responsive grid with CSS-only controls, ensuring accessibility and motion considerations on a realistic product surface.

## Key Concepts

- CSS Grid density presets via CSS variables
- CSS-only toggle using a hidden checkbox
- Animation staggering and prefers-reduced-motion
- Accessible focus styles and keyboard navigation
- Rail-to-bottom-sheet pattern on small screens

## Code Example

```html
<!-- Minimal sketch: HTML structure -->
<div class="feed-container">
  <input type="checkbox" id="density-toggle" class="density-toggle" hidden>
  <label for="density-toggle" class="density-label">Toggle Density</label>
  <div class="feed-grid">
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-image"></div>
      <div class="card-content">Card content</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
```

```css
/* CSS-only solution with variables and responsive behavior */
.feed-container {
  --cols: 4;
  --gap: 16px;
  --cardH: 240px;
  --aspect-ratio: 16/9;
}

.feed-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(var(--cols), 1fr);
  gap: var(--gap);
}

.card {
  height: var(--cardH);
  animation: fadeInUp 0.4s ease-out;
}

.density-toggle:checked ~ .feed-grid {
  --cols: 6;
  --gap: 8px;
  --cardH: 180px;
  --aspect-ratio: 1/1;
}
```

## Follow-up Questions

- How would you test accessibility and keyboard navigation?
- What approach would you use for internationalization of the density toggle?
- How would you handle image lazy loading in this grid pattern?

## Why This Is Asked
