## Why This Is Asked
Tests mastery of closures, per-domain rate limiting, and Promise deduplication—common in real apps with multiple data sources.

## Key Concepts
- Per-domain rate limiting (token bucket)
- In-flight deduplication of identical URLs via shared Promise
- TTL-based caching with automatic refresh
- Closure-based state encapsulation for domain data
- Robust error handling and cancellation considerations

## Code Example
```javascript
class RateLimitedFetcher {
  constructor(maxPerSec = 4, ttl = 30000) {
    this.maxPerSec = maxPerSec;
    this.ttl = ttl;
    this.domainBuckets = new Map(); // domain -> { tokens, queue }
    this.cache = new Map(); // url -> { data, expiry }
    this.inFlight = new Map(); // url -> Promise
  }
  _domain(domain) {
    if (!this.domainBuckets.has(domain)) {
      this.domainBuckets.set(domain, { tokens: maxPerSec, queue: [] });
    }
    return this.domainBuckets.get(domain);
  }
  async fetch(url, init) {
    const now = Date.now();
    const cached = this.cache.get(url);
    if (cached && cached.expiry > now) return cached.data;
    if (this.inFlight.has(url)) return this.inFlight.get(url);
    const domain = new URL(url).host;
    const bucket = this._domain(domain);
    const attempt = () => {
      if (bucket.tokens > 0) {
        bucket.tokens--;
        return true;
      }
      return false;
    };
    const run = async () => {
      try {
        const res = await fetch(url, init);
        const data = await res.clone().json().catch(() => res.text());
        this.cache.set(url, { data, expiry: Date.now() + this.ttl });
        return data;
      } finally {
        bucket.tokens++;
        // drain queued requests if any
        if (bucket.queue.length) {
          const next = bucket.queue.shift();
          next();
        }
      }
    };
    const promise = (async () => {
      if (!attempt()) {
        await new Promise(r => bucket.queue.push(r));
      }
      return run();
    })();
    this.inFlight.set(url, promise);
    const result = await promise;
    this.inFlight.delete(url);
    return result;
  }
  invalidate(url) { this.cache.delete(url); }
  warmRefresh(url) { this.invalidate(url); return this.fetch(url); }
}
```

## Follow-up Questions
- How would you unit-test this under bursty traffic and verify per-domain quotas?
- How would you extend to prioritize certain domains or implement exponential backoff on failures?

