questions.answer:
- API: useRenderCounter(threshold, { onWarn, once = true } = {}) returns the current render count. - Core: useRef stores count and a warned flag; increment count during render; useEffect runs after render to warn once when count > threshold. - Code:
```js
import { useEffect, useRef } from 'react'

export function useRenderCounter(threshold, { onWarn, once = true } = {}) {
  const countRef = useRef(0)
  const warned = useRef(false)
  // count this render
  countRef.current += 1
  useEffect(() => {
    if (countRef.current > threshold && (!once || !warned.current)) {
      warned.current = true
      if (onWarn) onWarn(countRef.current)
      else console.warn(`Render count ${countRef.current} exceeded threshold ${threshold}`)
    }
  })
  return countRef.current
}
```
- Usage:
```js
function Demo(){
  const r = useRenderCounter(100)
  return <div>Render #{r}</div>
}
```
- Flow: render -> increment ref -> post-render check -> warn (once) via onWarn or console.warn.
- Diagram:
```mermaid
graph TD
  A(Render) --> B{Count > threshold?}
  B -- Yes --> C[Warn (once)]
  B -- No --> D[No warning]
```

