## Concept Overview
A custom useDebounce hook defers function execution until a specified delay period has elapsed, making it essential for optimizing search inputs, API calls, and other performance-critical operations in React applications.

## Implementation Details
- Utilize useRef to maintain the latest callback reference, preventing stale closures across renders
- Implement comprehensive cleanup logic in useEffect to cancel pending debounced invocations
- Return a useCallback wrapper with stable dependencies for optimal concurrent rendering performance
- Handle component unmounting scenarios to prevent memory leaks and unexpected behavior
- Ensure proper cleanup of timers to maintain application stability

## Code Example
```javascript
import { useCallback, useRef, useEffect } from 'react';

export function useDebounce(callback, delay) {
  const callbackRef = useRef(callback);
  const timeoutRef = useRef(null);

  useEffect(() => {
    callbackRef.current = callback;
  }, [callback]);

  useEffect(() => {
    return () => {
      if (timeoutRef.current) {
        clearTimeout(timeoutRef.current);
      }
    };
  }, []);

  return useCallback((...args) => {
    if (timeoutRef.current) {
      clearTimeout(timeoutRef.current);
    }

    timeoutRef.current = setTimeout(() => {
      callbackRef.current(...args);
    }, delay);
  }, [delay]);
}
```

## Key Benefits
- Prevents stale closures through proper ref management
- Ensures cleanup on component unmount
- Maintains stable reference for concurrent rendering
- Handles edge cases and prevents memory leaks

